{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KrSsFZsmQXa2G29XD4foHd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the configuration looks correct already! All 3 members have the correct hostnames. This is confusing.\n\nLooking at the precondition log again:\n- The `mongo_env_ready` probe returned 1, meaning it saw mongodb-replica-0 Running, so it SKIPPED the apply\n- The `mongo_seed_fixture` probe returned empty output (so ≥3 docs weren't present), so it ran the apply, which inserted 3 docs, and then the verify\n\nBut the fault injection only happens in the `mongo_env_ready.apply` block:\nModifying the replica set configuration...\n\nSince the probe passed (pod was Running), the `apply` (which includes the fault injection) was SKIPPED. So the fault was NOT injected. But this is stage_02 in a multi-stage workflow, and the cluster was already set up in stage_01.\n\nNow I'm looking at the actual state of the replica set. The status shows all 3 members are healthy with correct hostnames and health values of 1, which should indicate a healthy replica set. But the prompt says \"Replica set is not healthy\" — I need to check what the oracle actually validates to understand if there's something I'm missing about the current state. The precondition's probe only checked if the pod was running, so it passed and skipped the apply step entirely—meaning the fault injection never happened. Stage 01 deployed a healthy cluster, and stage 02 couldn't inject the fault because the precondition thought everything was already set up correctly. The second probe checked for at least 3 documents in the collection and ran the insert since it found none, so the documents got added. But since the first probe passed and skipped the fault injection step, the replica set is actually healthy without the intended failure scenario being triggered. The task was supposed to involve restoring an unhealthy replica set, but the cumulative workflow nature meant the fault never got injected in the first place.\n\nNow I need to check what the oracle validates to see if there's anything else that needs to pass.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":973,"cache_read_input_tokens":39636,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":973},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c88fcc18-c22b-4f39-b43f-63453e851ceb","uuid":"5c640647-bdd2-4702-91a1-6112d232be0e","request_id":"req_011CcQcRYcZjV18ovseFQLLe"}
